  "text": "Hummingbirds! There are more than species of hummingbirds. They live in North America and South America. and many of them migrate south in the winter. RUBY-THROATED HUMMINGBIRD this short-legged hummingbird is the only species regularly spotted in most of the eastern United States. you you need to decide: Which kind of hummingbird are you? BEE HUMMINGBIRD Not just the smallest hummingbird. but actually the smallest bird in the world. about two inches long. weighs less than a dime. and lives only in Cuba. ANNA'S HUMMINGBIRD Named for an Italian duchess. it has feathers that are bright and iridescent. which means that when light hits them at a certain angle. they appear to change color. WIRE-CRESTED THORNTAIL With a long. pointed. blue tail and tall feathers that look like a wild hairstyle on top of its head. this small hummingbird stands out in a crowd! RUFOUS HUMMINGBIRD this fast and feisty flier will light any bird that competes with for food. It can migrate huge distances-up to miles! MARVELOUS SPATULETAIL this rare hummingbird has a long and unique tail made up of four feathers BLUE-THROATED HILLSTAR Discovered in in the Andes Mountains of Ecuador. this beautiful blue bird can survive in cold temperatures. unlike most other species. Ecuador has about 'hummingbird species Why so many? Hummingbirds thrive in places with biociversity. or many kinds of climates and habitats. this South American country has warm tropical rain forests. cool coastal areas. and the tall Andes Mountains! Many hummingbird species are endangered. which means only a few of the birds remain in the wild. and these species are at risk of becoming extinct. or disappearing forever. GIANT HUMMINGBIRD this is the largest and slowest-flying hummingbird. At about eight inches long. it's the size of a cardinal and has dull green or brown CALLIOPE HUMMINGBIRD Named for the ancient Greek muse of epic poetry. this itty-bitty hummingbird has a short biu and tail and is the smallest bird in the United States and Canada",
